ing on her thesis, and thus provides both a wide-ranging debate on the social implications of motherhood, and an invaluable survey of Gaskell criticism over the last twenty years. This study will bring a well-tried classic to a new audience, while also offering a uniquely comprehensive overview of current Gaskell studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Women Authors.2bisacsh  aElizabeth Gaskell.  aauthority.  aethical values.  afemale friendship.  amotherhood.  apolitical analysis.  apower of speech.  arational motherhood.  asocial analyst.  asocial change.1 aStoneman, Patsy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779190040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847791900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847791900/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles